# Codex round-4 review — DEC-V61-053 · Batch D + 6 live-run fix commits (F1-M2 post-R3 gate)

## Context

DEC-V61-053 (circular cylinder at Re=100, Type I multi-dim validation, first native v2.0 DEC) reached APPROVE on **Codex round 3** for Batches A+B1+B2+B3+C. That approval was genuinely clean on the static code paths Codex could see.

Then **Batch D** (backend 4-scalar emission, frontend Compare-tab cards, karman_shedding.png generator with stale-fixture skip-guard) landed. The subsequent live OpenFOAM audit fixture regen campaign surfaced **SIX runtime-emergent defects** that required fixes before the fixture could actually populate with real physics. All 6 are now landed + regression-guarded. This is the R4 review scope.

