   151	      gate's gold value can be below that floor (e.g. LDC BL/BR ψ_gold
   152	      ≈ 1e-6), the extraction becomes argmax-coincidence, not validated
   153	      physics. Live smoke-test "2/2 PASS" on a noise-floor result is a
   154	      LURE.
   155	    mitigation_in_batch: |
   156	      For every gate, compute and COMMIT: extraction_numerical_floor vs
   157	      |gate_gold_value|. If the ratio < 10×, either refuse the gate (move
   158	      to follow-up DEC) or use a different extraction method (Poisson
   159	      solve for ψ, native OpenFOAM FO instead of trapezoidal, etc.). UI
   160	      must render a `signal_above_noise` flag so students don't confuse
   161	      noise coincidences with physics.
